{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"16030a3d-9bb0-4f09-be05-c904e21a118b","content":"**Exit code 8** means \"no tests were found.\" MTP treats zero discovered tests as a failure, unlike VSTest which returned 0.\n\n**Fix:** Add the `--ignore-exit-code` flag via an environment variable or MSBuild property.\n\n**Option A — In your CI pipeline (recommended):**\n\nSet this environment variable before running `dotnet test`:\n\n```bash\nexport TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\n```\n\nThis tells MTP to treat exit code 8 (no tests found) as exit code 0.\n\n**Option B — In the `.csproj`:**","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01HEw2oNdC7wCZRWnL2LmnML","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Applying MTP exit code fix"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QaXxscpBr4QyUj2t1QsWug","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2951480148c245ef83531edabb1d4e67/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n    <!-- Treat \"no tests discovered\" (exit code 8) as success for conditional-compilation scenarios -->\n    <TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--ignore-exit-code 8</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2951480148c245ef83531edabb1d4e67/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"c46fa47e-ab0e-4631-bc49-81df4c63450b","outputTokens":405,"requestId":"4842:AFA09:32921EF:3728168:69FBE350"},"id":"38afca59-7cbf-4115-8ec4-7424ab2fef4c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:56:56.664Z","parentId":"71ed8c54-0aa6-4071-9914-4472df139f66"}
