{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3b7f66ef-3394-4257-84db-6e7459acb1ac","content":"It now returns **exit code 0** even with zero tests discovered. Here's a summary:\n\n### What changed\n\nMTP exit codes differ from VSTest. Code **8** = \"no tests found\" — a failure in MTP, but harmless in your conditional-compilation scenario.\n\n### The fix (in your `.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>--ignore-exit-code 8</TestingPlatformCommandLineArguments>\n```\n\nThis tells MTP to map exit code 8 → 0. Alternatively, set `TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8` as an environment variable in CI if you prefer not to embed it in the project file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c46fa47e-ab0e-4631-bc49-81df4c63450b","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"4842:AFA09:32971A5:372DC97:69FBE364"},"id":"24cf299b-ea03-47b0-a8aa-66de73ab5297","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:15.968Z","parentId":"682f2fb2-7cd8-4cf1-ae91-a437a7631824"}
